I’m not sparking joy through my organizational skills but these photos of me coaching give me so much happiness. 

Explanations that you didn’t know you were getting: 
1. Getting the kids to give their nervous energy to me. 
2. Becoming カオナシ to help with make up. it was so hot outside 🥵
3. Bringing Lincoln for emotional support. 
4. Does anyone else get super competitive on @duolingo 

#coaching #womeninbusiness #coach #figureskating #figureskate #iceskater #iceskating #skate #languagelearning

node.text:
Watching the Olympics right now very much reminds me of when I used to wonder/dream of one day going to the Olympics myself. I want to highlight two small local businesses/journeys that I happened upon during my traveling+coaching. 

I never thought I’d be a scrunchie type of person but I met a wonderful skater (age 7) @thenyahpapaya who told me that she makes scrunchies to help pay for her skating, and now I’m a scrunchie person. I also watched while she took the skating skills exercises she learned during group class and started practicing them on her own. Please support her skating/send support if you can. 

Another skater I met @kenna.shumway brought me mittens, socks, and scrunchies from @lovewoolies which are handmade from repurposed cashmere sweaters.  Kenna stood out to me because she started skating three years ago yet is able to land all of her doubles. I get asked by skaters if it’s too late to start skating and I always say that skating is for everyone. Kenna is the epitome of hard work and is proof that age is just a number. If you’re looking for the warmest pair of mittens, I 10/10 recommend @lovewoolies which Kenna’s mom owns. 

Although it’s a huge honor to represent @teamusa at the Olympics, please remember that sports is for everyone! In the meantime, I’m sending nothing but positive energy towards all of @teamusa during @tokyo2020 🇺🇸😎
